&lt;Greyhound Lines> said it agreed toacquire the routes of &lt;Trailways Corp>.    Greyhound said it had petitioned the Interstate CommerceCommission for authority to acquire and operate Trailways'routes, 450 of its 1200 buses and some of its terminals andgarages.    Trailways has abandoned all service in seven states in thepast year and more than half of its sevice in three otherstates, the company said.    "Without intervention, the collaspe of Trailways isimminent," said Fred Currey, chairman and president ofGreyhound. Reuter&#3;